There's two more ways of making a DOM Event - In this lesson, we will learn how to make a DOM event entirely through JavaScript.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

First Way: 

<h1>Click me!</h1>

let h1 = document.getElementsByTagName('h1')[0];
h1.onclick = changeH1; 

function changeH1(){
  h1.innerHTML = 'New h1!';
}

//you don't need to set the "()" on the functions, otherwise, the functions will trigger instantly - even if the Event doesn't happened yet.


----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Second way: (addEventListener)

<h1>Click me!</h1>

let h1 = document.getElementsByTagName('h1')[0];
h1.addEventListener('click', changeH1);

function changeH1(){
  h1.innerHTML = 'New h1!';
}

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
